NOTICE — Composite licensing
============================

This font is a composite work combining glyphs from multiple donor
fonts. While the assembled font is distributed under the SIL Open
Font License, Version 1.1 (above), a portion of its glyphs derives
from FSung (Full-Sung, Taiwan 全宋體), created and maintained by
F.G. Wang (https://fgwang.blogspot.com/).

F.G. Wang grants FSung for academic research, educational work,
and personal reading. F.G. Wang prohibits commercial use of FSung
glyphs ("請勿用做任何形式的商業營利行為" — "please do not use for
any commercial profit-making activity").

For FSung-derived glyphs in this font, in addition to the OFL
terms above:

  * Academic research, educational work, and personal reading
    are permitted.
  * Commercial use — any form of commercial profit-making
    activity — is prohibited for FSung-derived glyphs.

F.G. Wang's original statement (Chinese):

  現將此成果無條件分享出來，樂見學術研究、教育工作、個人閱讀
  這方面的運用，但請勿用做任何形式的商業營利行為。希望「全宋
  體」這個大型字庫以及「部件檢索」這個檢字工具，能在漢字文化
  的整理、研究上幫上一點小忙。

For OFL-derived glyphs (everything not from FSung), the OFL above
applies without additional restrictions.

The full attribution record is in
`references/input-fonts/ATTRIBUTIONS.md`. The list of FSung-derived
codepoints (so downstream users can honor the restriction
programmatically) is auto-generated per release as
`LICENSE-SOURCES.md`, distributed alongside the TTF on GitHub
Releases.

To request commercial-use permission for FSung-derived glyphs,
contact F.G. Wang at: https://fgwang.blogspot.com/
